), female 
<quantity box="[699,865,835,861]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.145" metricValueMax="1.26" metricValueMin="1.03" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" unit="mm" value="11.45" valueMax="12.6" valueMin="10.3">10.3–12.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,1365]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,870,896]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Kral &amp; Strnad, 1992" authorityName="Kral &amp; Strnad" authorityYear="1992" box="[592,978,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heyrovskyi">
<emphasis box="[592,743,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. heyrovskyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kral, D. &amp; Strnad, J." box="[749,978,871,897]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" pagination="3 - 6" refId="ref17217" refString="Kral, D. &amp; Strnad, J. (1992) New Eophileurus species from Vietnam (Scarabaeidae, Dynastinae). Folia Heyrovskyana, 1, 3 - 6." type="journal article" year="1992">Král &amp; Strnad, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[994,1129,870,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–70" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1486,1510]" captionTargetBox="[164,1420,247,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-46@14.[151,1435,237,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 65–70. Habitus of Eophileurus heyrovskyi Král &amp; Strnad, 1992. 65–66, male (Mt. Laoshan); 67, male (Longli); 68–69, female (Luoyingou); 70, male (Luoyingou); 65, 67, 68, 70, dorsal view; 66, 69, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853964" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853964/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs. 65–70</figureCitation>
) due to the similar external characters and the backward processes at the outer sides of the parameres. It can be distinguished from the latter by the following points: elytral punctures relatively smaller; elytral margin more weakly dilated (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1438,1462]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,193,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-18@20.[151,1435,181,1414]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Habitus of Eophileurus prelli Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, new species. 93–94, holotype; 95, male paratype; 96–98, female paratypes; 93, 95, 96, 98 dorsal view; 94, 97, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853972/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs. 93, 95–96, 98</figureCitation>
); metasternum with a lance-shaped depression at center (
<figureCitation box="[816,951,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1438,1462]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,193,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-18@20.[151,1435,181,1414]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Habitus of Eophileurus prelli Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, new species. 93–94, holotype; 95, male paratype; 96–98, female paratypes; 93, 95, 96, 98 dorsal view; 94, 97, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853972/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs. 94, 97</figureCitation>
), whereas absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kral &amp; Strnad" authorityYear="1992" box="[1175,1324,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heyrovskyi">
<emphasis box="[1175,1324,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. heyrovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 65–70" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1486,1510]" captionTargetBox="[164,1420,247,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-46@14.[151,1435,237,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 65–70. Habitus of Eophileurus heyrovskyi Král &amp; Strnad, 1992. 65–66, male (Mt. Laoshan); 67, male (Longli); 68–69, female (Luoyingou); 70, male (Luoyingou); 65, 67, 68, 70, dorsal view; 66, 69, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853964" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853964/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs. 66, 69</figureCitation>
); protarsi more strongly thickened (
<figureCitation box="[579,715,1014,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1438,1462]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,193,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-18@20.[151,1435,181,1414]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Habitus of Eophileurus prelli Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, new species. 93–94, holotype; 95, male paratype; 96–98, female paratypes; 93, 95, 96, 98 dorsal view; 94, 97, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853972/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs. 93–95</figureCitation>
); shapes of parameres different (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1235,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–184" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1476,1500]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,189,1441]" captionTargetId="figure-18@30.[151,1435,181,1453]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 165–184. Parameres of Eophileurus Arrow, 1908 species. 165–166, E. confinis Prell, 1913 (Bao Loc); 167–168, E. heyrovskyi Kral &amp; Strnad, 1992 (Longli); 169–172, E. minor Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, new species, 169–170, holotype, 171–172, paratype (Dong Tien, images ©Ming-Zhi Zhao); 173–174, E. prelli Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, new species, holotype; 174–180, E. quadratifovealis Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, new species, 175–176, holotype, 177–178, paratype (Mu Si), 179–180, paratype (Chatabon, images by Keita Matsumoto ©Natural History Museum, London); 181–184, E. sidereus Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, new species, 181–182, holotype, 183–184, paratype; odd number ones, front view; even number ones, lateral view; scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853988/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs. 167–168</figureCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kral &amp; Strnad" authorityYear="1992" box="[1280,1430,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heyrovskyi">
<emphasis box="[1280,1430,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. heyrovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 173–174 for 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, 2022" authorityName="Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak" authorityYear="2022" box="[296,387,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prelli" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[296,387,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. prelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[401,538,1050,1077]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[401,538,1050,1077]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,1365]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1087,1113]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of the German zoologist Prof. Heinrich Prell (1888–1962) for his significant contribution to the study of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1819" box="[749,879,1123,1149]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dynastinae">Dynastinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,462,1158,1185]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,1365]" box="[199,462,1158,1185]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1158,1184]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,458,1159,1185]" name="Vietnam" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,1365]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1195,1221]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Remarks.</emphasis>
Amongst other 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Endrodi" authorityYear="1977" box="[503,640,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[503,640,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Eophileurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[712,810,1195,1221]" name="Vietnam" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak, 2022" authorityName="Yang &amp; Pathomwattananurak" authorityYear="2022" box="[823,916,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prelli" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[823,916,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. prelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[932,1071,1194,1221]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[932,1071,1194,1221]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is related to both 
<taxonomicName authority="Kral &amp; Strnad, 1992" authorityName="Kral &amp; Strnad" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heyrovskyi">
<emphasis box="[1284,1437,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. heyrovskyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kral, D. &amp; Strnad, J." box="[151,379,1231,1257]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" pagination="3 - 6" refId="ref17217" refString="Kral, D. &amp; Strnad, J. (1992) New Eophileurus species from Vietnam (Scarabaeidae, Dynastinae). Folia Heyrovskyana, 1, 3 - 6." type="journal article" year="1992">Král &amp; Strnad, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Muramoto, 2004" authorityName="Muramoto" authorityYear="2004" box="[433,791,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baolocensis">
<emphasis box="[433,596,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. baolocensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Muramoto, R." box="[603,791,1231,1257]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" pagination="21 - 24" refId="ref17354" refString="Muramoto, R. (2004) Notes on the genus Eophileurus Arrow (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Dynastinae) from Southeast Asia, with description of a new species from southern Vietnam. Kogane, 5, 21 - 24." type="journal article" year="2004">Muramoto, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the rounded posterior angle of pronotum. Although its 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1267,1293]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">type</typeStatus>
locality is closer to the distributing area of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muramoto" authorityYear="2004" box="[675,837,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baolocensis">
<emphasis box="[675,837,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. baolocensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is more closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kral &amp; Strnad" authorityYear="1992" box="[1153,1301,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heyrovskyi">
<emphasis box="[1153,1301,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">E. heyrovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to them both having backward processes on the outer sides of the parameres.Additionally, since its 
<typeStatus box="[1157,1205,1303,1329]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">type</typeStatus>
locality is extremely close to 
<collectingCountry box="[245,302,1339,1365]" name="Laos" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Laos</collectingCountry>
, occurrence of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[637,691,1339,1365]" name="Laos" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Laos</collectingCountry>
would not be surprising.
</paragraph>
